@node "INFO" "SN RTFRI v1.0 - Information"
@toc "MAIN"
┌─────────────────────────────┐
  SN RTFRI v1.0 - Information
└─────────────────────────────┘

Ever wanted to run Cygnus Ed, MultiView, MoreText or any other program on
CNet's screen and wanted support for file requesters?  Now all you have to
do is put the command in a config file and go!  (It's a little more than
that, see the Installation section for more details.)  Allows you to
define where the command can be run from remote or not, also, automatically
disabling file-requesters so you don't get a hung port!  Trapping of assigns
not made is done internally also, so you're safe there, too!

Uses ReqTools requesters if available!  (You need to have reqtools.library
and rexxreqtools.library in your libs:)

(I would have included the necessary files in this archive, but, as stated
in the rexxreqtools docs, the minimum distribution requires the docs to
rexxreqtools.  Huh, you ask?  I printed them out a long time ago and now I
can't find the originals on my drive.  If anyone has them, please mail
them to me!  :)

Features to note:
  - Multi-line compatible.  You don't have to worry about conflictions.
  - Self-cleaning.  Leaves no temp files lying around.
  - Uses ReqTools requesters, if available.
  - Able to define new programs locally or remotely.
  - Programs can be restricted to local-use only.

NOTE:  This is a compiled ARexx script.  However, it does not require any
       additional libraries or RPStart to function (unless otherwise
       noted in these docs).

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
